maintext: Singapore Airlines (SIA) has revealed new details of its planned nonstop flight to Newark Liberty International Airport (EWR), which will be the world’s longest route. The flight from Singapore to EWR will begin Oct. 11 with three services per week, using the first of the carrier’s Airbus A350-900ULRs. title: Singapore Airlines to launch A350-900ULR nonstop Newark service in October
